		<section id="changelog:service:mail">
			<title>Mail services</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The long waiting for the DH parameter generation on the first install has been
					removed in the Dovecot package (<u:bug>38990</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					DH parameters are not created at installation time any more.
					Pre-calculated DH
					parameters for 512 and 2048 bit are provided. A one time generation of DH
					parameters is scheduled for the next day (<u:bug>37459</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The default of the UCR variable
					<envar>mail/postfix/cron/recreate/dh/parameter</envar> is changed to not
					recreate the DH parameters every night. The <wordasword>cronjob</wordasword> of existing installations is
					not changed (<u:bug>37459</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The activation of <envar>mail/postfix/policy/listfilter</envar> led to the mail
					server rejecting all emails. This has been fixed (<u:bug>39093</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A configuration error prevented Postfix from sending emails if Dovecot was also
					installed. Postfix' SMTP client now always uses the Cyrus SASL implementation
					(<u:bug>39151</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A configuration error in the Dovecot PAM stack has been fixed that led to
					higher than usual time to authenticate against Postfix SMTP. In some cases
					Postfix' authentication timeout has been reached and resulted in authentication
					failure (<u:bug>39267</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The Dovecot server did not close its standard error file descriptor
					(<u:bug>39148</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The Dovecot logrotate configuration has been fixed (<u:bug>39130</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Dovecot now works internally with lowercase email addresses
					(<u:bug>39346</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

