	<section id="changelog:other">
		<title>Other changes</title>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Incorrect quotation marks have been removed from <filename>/etc/lsb-release</filename>
				(<u:bug>37725</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The list of supported message digest, encryption and key exchange algorithms
				allowed by the SSH daemon can now be configured through the new UCR variables
				<envar>sshd/MACs</envar>, <envar>sshd/Ciphers</envar>, and
				<envar>sshd/KexAlgorithms</envar> (<u:bug>38609</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The insecure SSH protocols <wordasword>rsa1</wordasword> and
				<wordasword>dsa</wordasword> have been disabled. They can be re-enabled through
				the new UCR variables <envar>sshd/Protocol</envar> and
				<envar>sshd/HostKey</envar> (<u:bug>38709</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The handling of UCR variable <envar>sshd/banner</envar> has been fixed
				(<u:bug>39166</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The program <command>univention-openssh-recreate-host-keys</command> now
				re-creates all host key files supported by SSH (<u:bug>38710</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The number of bits used when re-creating new host keys can be overwritten
				through the UCR variables like <envar>sshd/HostKey/rsa</envar>
				(<u:bug>38711</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The package <package>lockfile-progs</package> has been moved to maintained, as
